cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with event representation learning using external commonsense knowledge, which is a topic that falls under natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to improve event embeddings, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper uses external knowledge to enhance the embeddings, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to predict stock market volatilities, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of embeddings for downstream tasks, which falls under the scope of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
